<heading box="[280,627,1716,1743]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" reason="2">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaup, 1833" authorityName=", Kaup" authorityYear="1833" box="[357,627,1716,1743]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Machairodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[357,492,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Machairodus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="KAUP J. J." box="[499,627,1716,1743]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" refId="ref9667" refString="KAUP J. J. 1833. - Description d'ossements fossiles de mammiferes inconnus jusqu'a present qui se trouvent au Museum grand-ducal de Darmstadt. Second cahier. Heyer, Darmstadt, 135 p." type="book" year="1833">Kaup, 1833</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="124" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[132,775,1792,2029]" lastBlockId="3.[813,1456,217,690]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">
<collectionCode box="[132,182,1792,1815]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">TYPE</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[189,262,1797,1814]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">SPECIES</collectionCode>
. — 
<emphasis box="[310,454,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Felis aphanista</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="KAUP J." box="[461,581,1793,1817]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" pagination="150 - 158" refId="ref9633" refString="KAUP J. 1832. - Vier neue Arten urweltlicher Raubthiere, welche im zoologischen Museum zu Darmstadt aufbewahrt werden. Archiv fur Mineralogie, Bergbau und Huttenkunde 5: 150 - 158." type="journal article" year="1832">Kaup, 1832</bibRefCitation>
is usually regarded as the type species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaup, 1833" authorityName=", Kaup" authorityYear="1833" box="[359,620,1819,1844]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Machairodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[359,487,1819,1843]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Machairodus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="KAUP J. J." box="[495,620,1820,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" refId="ref9667" refString="KAUP J. J. 1833. - Description d'ossements fossiles de mammiferes inconnus jusqu'a present qui se trouvent au Museum grand-ducal de Darmstadt. Second cahier. Heyer, Darmstadt, 135 p." type="book" year="1833">Kaup, 1833</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but this is incorrect. Kaup based his description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kaup" authorityYear="1833" box="[520,646,1846,1870]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Machairodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[520,646,1846,1870]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Machairodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on an upper canine from Eppelsheim in Darmstadt, but his title “ 
<taxonomicName authority=", Kaup" authorityName=", Kaup" authorityYear="1833" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Machairodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Machairodus</emphasis>
, Kaup
</taxonomicName>
” is followed by the sub-title “Ours [French for ‘bear’], Cuv; Cultridens, Jobert et Croiset [sic]”, and in his description (
<bibRefCitation author="KAUP J. J." box="[140,294,1952,1976]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" refId="ref9667" refString="KAUP J. J. 1833. - Description d'ossements fossiles de mammiferes inconnus jusqu'a present qui se trouvent au Museum grand-ducal de Darmstadt. Second cahier. Heyer, Darmstadt, 135 p." type="book" year="1833">Kaup 1833: 25</bibRefCitation>
) he stated “je pense qu’il serait convenable […] d’employer le nom de 
<emphasis box="[358,452,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">cultridens</emphasis>
pour le genre auquel appartiennent les canines trouvées dans la 
<collectingRegion box="[461,542,2005,2028]" country="Italy" name="Toscana" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Toscane</collectingRegion>
et dans le grand-duché de Hesse-Darmstadt.” According to Art. 12.2.5 of the 
<collectionCode box="[1384,1451,217,241]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">ICZN</collectionCode>
, these indications could be regarded as a designation of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Ursus cultridens</emphasis>
Cuvier, 1824 as the type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kaup" authorityYear="1833" box="[1270,1396,270,294]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Machairodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[1270,1396,270,294]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Machairodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, even if the Eppelsheim canine turns out to be of the same species as the 
<typeStatus box="[853,942,322,346]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[979,1125,322,346]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Felis aphanista</emphasis>
, and no matter what Kaup and other authors wrote afterwards (
<emphasis box="[1132,1192,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">contra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="MORLO M. &amp; SEMENOV Y. A." box="[1197,1440,349,373]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" pagination="123 - 138" refId="ref10296" refString="MORLO M. &amp; SEMENOV Y. A. 2004. - New dental remains of Machairodus Kaup 1833 (Felidae, Carnivora, Mammalia) from the Turolian of Ukraine: significance for the evolution of the genus. Kaupia 13: 123 - 138." type="journal article" year="2004">Morlo &amp; Semenov 2004</bibRefCitation>
). This would make 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kaup" authorityYear="1833" box="[990,1116,375,399]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Machairodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[990,1116,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Machairodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[1331,1455,376,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Megantereon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="CROIZET J. B. &amp; JOBERT A. C. G." box="[813,1057,402,426]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" refId="ref8974" refString="CROIZET J. B. &amp; JOBERT A. C. G. 1828. - Recherches sur les ossemens fossiles du departement du Puy-de-Dome. Paris, 122 p." type="book" year="1828">Croizet &amp; Jobert, 1828</bibRefCitation>
, if the type species of the latter genus, 
<emphasis box="[813,977,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Me. megantereon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="CROIZET J. B. &amp; JOBERT A. C. G." box="[982,1218,428,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" refId="ref8974" refString="CROIZET J. B. &amp; JOBERT A. C. G. 1828. - Recherches sur les ossemens fossiles du departement du Puy-de-Dome. Paris, 122 p." type="book" year="1828">Croizet &amp; Jobert, 1828</bibRefCitation>
, is indeed a synonym of 
<emphasis box="[813,953,455,479]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Me. cultridens</emphasis>
(Cuvier, 1824), as generally believed. Things are not so ‘simple’, however. As pointed out to us by L. Werdelin, the use of 
<emphasis box="[915,1009,508,532]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">cultridens</emphasis>
by Kaup is not unambiguous, as several taxa were included by him under this name, which might invalidate the new genus name. Another problem is that Cuvier’s statement: “c’est ce qui me détermine à changer le nom d’ 
<emphasis box="[1268,1349,588,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">etruscus,</emphasis>
que j’avais donné à cet ours en celui de 
<emphasis box="[1095,1189,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">cultridens</emphasis>
.” creates a nice example of objective synonym. For the sake of stability, we will use 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kaup" authorityYear="1833" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Machairodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Machairodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its usual meaning.
</paragraph>
